sql:
SELECT AVG(put_premium) AS AveragePutPremium
FROM options_trades
WHERE trade_date > '2022-01-01';

external_knowledge:
- "captains" refers to the traders;
- "ships" metaphorically represents the trades;
- "favorable winds" refers to a positive total direction;
- "names of their vessels" are the trade identifiers;
- "identities of the navigators" are the trader names;
- "blueprint of their voyage" corresponds to the strategy name;
- "average cost of their safety nets" refers to the average put and call premiums;
- "trade waters" refers to the ongoing trading activities.

sql:
SELECT trade_id
FROM trade_analysis
WHERE profit_loss > (SELECT AVG(profit_loss) FROM trade_analysis);
